 Your next destination is ILHABELA - VIDEO 

00:00:53.899 --> 00:00:56.559
 ILHABELA is one of the most sought after destinations on the north coast of São Paulo, 

00:00:56.559 --> 00:00:59.579
 beaches of Ilhabela or by the numerous walks by waterfalls and trails. 

00:00:59.579 --> 00:01:05.100
 In total there are 29 beautiful beaches and more than 300 waterfalls. Direct contact with nature 

00:01:05.100 --> 00:01:07.360
 is constant throughout the island, either on the beaches or in the waterfalls with the right ecological trails. 

00:01:07.360 --> 00:01:14.360
 One of ILHABELA's most famous adventures is the trail - 22km - to cross the 

00:01:24.890 --> 00:01:31.890
 island and reaches the beach of CASTELHANOS, which is the largest beach on the island with 2km of extension. 

00:01:44.579 --> 00:01:47.099
 For dive lovers, ILHA DAS CABRAS is the perfect place to meet 

00:01:47.099 --> 00:01:47.319
 butterflyfish, batfish, tamarins, marias-nagô, maidens and schools of sergeants. 

00:01:47.560 --> 00:01:48.280
 The bottom rocks are lined with ascidians, sponges, sea anemones, corals, zoanthids, 

00:01:48.280 --> 00:01:48.530
 gorgonians, starfish and a multitude of other multicolored animals. worth a lot 

00:01:48.289 --> 00:01:51.259
 worth plunging into ILHABELA. 

00:01:51.259 --> 00:01:53.619
 Another attraction is the famous statue of Neptune, five meters deep, 

00:01:53.619 --> 00:01:56.549
 on the eastern side of the ISLAND OF CABRAS. With so much life in those waters, it would be difficult 

00:01:56.549 --> 00:02:03.549
 to imagine a better place to pay homage to the King of the Seas. 

00:02:08.560 --> 00:02:15.560
 The side of the Island that faces the mainland has the perfect wind for practicing sports 

00:02:44.530 --> 00:02:51.530
 nautical And that's how ILHABELA earned her so-called nickname - Candle Capital 

00:02:53.870 --> 00:03:00.870
 - for being chosen the preferred point of sailors and other nautical sportsmen. 

